        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Orc Duels",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom pg. 88",
                  "aonid": 251,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom pg. 88",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom",
                "page": 88,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Dueling is a frequent practice among many cultures of Golarion, and orcs are no exception. The lethality of these duels varies based on the duel's impetus\u2014a friendly bout goes to first blood or until a combatant is knocked out, while a fight in response to a vendetta or insult is more likely to the death. Unlike in many dueling traditions, spectators are encouraged to verbally aid combatants, shouting out encouragement to one's preferred fighter and invectives to their opponent.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom pg. 88",
              "aonid": 251,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom pg. 88",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Pathfinder #209: Destroyer's Doom",
            "page": 88,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "While some orc warriors specialize in a technique of their hold, others synthesize styles from all over into a unified yet versatile technique.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
