                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "nonlethal",
                    "aonid": 2311,
                    "game-obj": "Rules",
                    "name": "nonlethal",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Nonlethal",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Attacks with this weapon are nonlethal, and are used to knock creatures unconscious instead of kill them. You can use a nonlethal weapon to make a lethal attack with a \u20132 circumstance penalty.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 251,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "a68f0660873f2bfbf523e9dedee9c530",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Ranged Trip",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 283,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "The weapon can be used to Trip with the Athletics skill within the weapon\u2019s first range increment. The skill check takes a \u20132 circumstance penalty. You can add the weapon\u2019s item bonus to attack rolls as a bonus to the check. A ranged trip weapon doesn\u2019t deal any damage when used to Trip. These weapons are usually thrown.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 195,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "c42503980965022311443a6e1e55ab57",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Thrown",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 283,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "You can throw this weapon as a ranged attack; it is a ranged weapon when thrown. You add your Strength modifier to damage as you would for a melee weapon. When this trait appears on a melee weapon, it also includes the range increment. Ranged weapons with this trait use the range increment in the weapon\u2019s Range entry.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "weapon": "bola"
